The paper proposes a new model for learning arbitrary-order cross features adaptively from data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. The paper focuses on improving the performance of predictive models, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
